    "description": "We at GE Healthcare India Consulting Pvt Ltd are looking for an experienced Surgeon based out of Aurangabad. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout GE Healthcare India Consulting Pvt Ltd:\nGE Healthcare India Consulting Pvt Ltd is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Chartered Accountant (ICAI)\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Clinical Research\n• Proficiency in ICU Management\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n• Proficiency in BLS/ACLS\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Flexible working hours\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Learning & development budget\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Aurangabad, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with GE Healthcare India Consulting Pvt Ltd!",
